parameters.name: Id
parameters.description: The ID of the namespace that you want to get information about.

nested_items.name: Namespace
nested_items.description: A complex type that contains information about the specified namespace.

nested_items.name: Arn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) that Cloud Map assigns to the namespace when you create it.

nested_items.name: Name
nested_items.description: The name of the namespace, such as example.com.

nested_items.name: Type
nested_items.description: The type of the namespace. The methods for discovering instances depends on the value that you specify:

nested_items.name: Description
nested_items.description: The description that you specify for the namespace when you create it.

nested_items.name: ServiceCount
nested_items.description: The number of services that are associated with the namespace.

nested_items.name: Properties
nested_items.description: A complex type that contains information that's specific to the type of the namespace.

nested_items.name: DnsProperties
nested_items.description: A complex type that contains the ID for the Route 53 hosted zone that Cloud Map creates when you create a namespace.

nested_items.name: HostedZoneId
nested_items.description: The ID for the Route 53 hosted zone that Cloud Map creates when you create a namespace.

nested_items.name: TTL
nested_items.description: The time to live (TTL) for purposes of negative caching.

nested_items.name: HttpProperties
nested_items.description: A complex type that contains the name of an HTTP namespace.

nested_items.name: HttpName
nested_items.description: The name of an HTTP namespace.

nested_items.name: CreateDate
nested_items.description: The date that the namespace was created, in Unix date/time format and Coordinated Universal Time (UTC). The value of CreateDate is accurate to milliseconds. For example, the value 1516925490.087 represents Friday, January 26, 2018 12:11:30.087 AM.

nested_items.name: CreatorRequestId
nested_items.description: A unique string that identifies the request and that allows failed requests to be retried without the risk of running an operation twice.
